                <head>149. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The Development Assistance Committee (<gloss target="#t_DAC1">DAC</gloss>) of the
                    Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development held its tenth meeting in
                    Paris July 25-26, 1962, to discuss the results of the first annual Aid Review
                    and future work. Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_RJW1">James W.
                        Riddleberger</persName> served as head of the U.S. Delegation and chairman
                    of the meeting. <persName corresp="#p_CFM2">Frank M. Coffin</persName>, <gloss
                        target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> Deputy Director, was also a member of the U.S.
                    Delegation. For text of the communnique issued at the end of the meeting, along
                    with a resolution adopted by the Committee on July 26, see Department of State
                    Bulletin, September 10, 1962, pages 395-397. For <persName corresp="#p_RJW1"
                        >Riddleberger</persName>’s telegraphic report on the meeting to the
                    Department of State, July 31, see the Supplement. Other documentation on the
                        <gloss target="#t_DAC1">DAC</gloss> meeting is in Department of State,
                    Central File 800.0000.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
